The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Makeover for Hotmail
                                                                                                                           17                                                                                      Makeover for Hotmail
                            
	San Francisco, May 18 (AP): Microsoft Corp. is trying to make Hotmail cool again.        
	The free Web mail service soon will be switching to a new approach that Microsoft hopes will give Hotmail an edge over rival offerings from Yahoo Inc. and Google Inc. The upgrade, expected to be available in July or August, will automatically sort incoming messages into different categories devoted to users key contacts and Internet social networks.                                                                                                                                                          
